    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This E46 M3 is a mechanically robust example featuring the S54B32 3.2L inline-six engine, renowned for its individual throttle bodies and high-pressure Double VANOS variable valve timing. Power is delivered through a crisp Getrag 420G six-speed manual transmission to a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. Crucial preventive maintenance has been addressed, including rear subframe reinforcement and rod bearing replacement with high-performance shells. The suspension utilizes a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear setup, currently fitted with Bilstein dampers for improved transient response. Braking is handled by ventilated rotors with upgraded compound pads for better thermal management. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the drivetrain remains tight and the 8,000 RPM redline is met with a linear, visceral power delivery. A purpose-built machine for the discerning driver.",
